%I A088913 #24 Jul 23 2026 17:05:21
%S A088913 15,315,5760,103635,1860375,33384960,599073735,10749954915,
%T A088913 192900147840,3461452792875,62113250350815,1114577054115840,
%U A088913 20000273725289535,358890350005167435,6440026026378384000,115561578124833652035
%N A088913 a(n) = (Lucas(2n) + Lucas(2n+1)*phi)/kappa(phi/Fibonacci(4n)) where kappa(x) is the sum of successive remainders in computing the Euclidean algorithm for (1,x).
%F A088913 Conjecture: a(n) = Lucas(6*n) - Lucas(2*n). - _Peter Bala_, Jul 21 2026
%e A088913 From _Peter Bala_, Jul 21 2026: (Start)
%e A088913 n = 1: phi/Fibonacci(4) = phi/3.
%e A088913 The Euclidean algorithm on (1, phi/3) produces the quotient sequence [1, 1, 5, 1, 5, 1, 5, ...]. The first few steps are shown below:
%e A088913  Step     Dividend           Divisor        Quotient      Remainder r_k
%e A088913 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
%e A088913   1          1               phi/3             1            (3 - phi)/3
%e A088913   2        phi/3           (3 - phi)/3         1            (2*phi - 3)/3
%e A088913   3      (3 - phi)/3       (2*phi - 3)/3       5            (18 - 11*phi)/3
%e A088913   4      (2*phi - 3)/3     (18 - 11*phi)/3     1            (13*phi - 21)/3
%e A088913   5      (18 - 11*phi)/3   (13*phi - 21)/3     5            (123 - 76*phi)/3
%e A088913   6      (13*phi - 21)/3   (123 - 6*phi)/3     1            (89*phi - 144)/3
%e A088913  ...
%e A088913 From step 2 onwards, the quotients alternate between 1 and 5 and the remainders scale down by a constant factor of 1/phi^4 every two steps, that is, r_{k+2} = r_{k}/phi^4.
%e A088913 This splits the remainders into two infinite geometric series (odd and even indices) sharing the same common ratio of 1/phi^4.
%e A088913 Therefore, Kappa(phi/3) = sum of odd remainders + sum of even remainders
%e A088913  = r_1/(1 - phi^(-4)) + r_2/(1 - phi^(-4)) = (5 + 2*sqrt(5))/15.
%e A088913 Hence, a(1) = (Lucas(2) + Lucas(3)*phi)/Kappa(phi/3) = 15. (End)
%Y A088913 Cf. A088914.
%K A088913 easy,nonn,changed
%O A088913 1,1
%A A088913 _Thomas Baruchel_, Nov 29 2003
%E A088913 Two errors in Data corrected by _Peter Bala_, Jul 21 2026
